Privacy Policy for Math Games – Speed & Logic

1. Introduction
Math Games – Speed & Logic is developed and operated by Kishore Musham. We are committed to protecting the privacy of all users, especially children. This Privacy Policy explains how information is handled in the app, including the use of advertising.

2. Personal Data Collection
We do not directly collect, store, or require any personal information from users.
No names, email addresses, phone numbers, or passwords are requested
No user registration or account creation is required

3. Advertising
The app displays ads to support ongoing development and maintenance.
Ads are provided by third-party advertising services
Ads are non-personalized and not interest-based, especially for children
We do not allow ads that track users across apps or websites
Third-party ad providers may use limited, non-personal identifiers (such as device type or app version) only to serve contextual ads, in accordance with applicable laws and platform policies.
We do not access, control, or store any data collected by these advertising partners.

4. Local Storage
All game-related data is stored locally on the user’s device, including:
Scores
Coins
Levels
Game progress
Selected avatars
This data never leaves the device. Deleting the app permanently removes all locally stored data.

5. Children’s Privacy (COPPA & Families Policy Compliance)
Math Games – Speed & Logic is designed for a general audience, including children.
We do not knowingly collect personal information from children
No behavioral tracking or profiling is performed
Only child-appropriate, non-personalized ads are shown
No persistent identifiers are used for tracking children
We comply fully with:
Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA)
Google Play Families Policy

6. Third-Party Services
The app may use third-party advertising SDKs solely for displaying ads.
No analytics or tracking SDKs are used beyond advertising delivery
No social media integrations
No external links that collect personal data
Each third-party service operates under its own privacy policy.

7. Changes to This Policy
This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page. Users are encouraged to review this policy periodically.

8. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, you can contact us at:
Email: kishcbit@gmail.com
